.TH GIT-PR-SYNC-STACK 1 "2026-06-14" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-sync-stack \- restack a GitHub pull request stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-sync-stack
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ number|url|branch ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-sync-stack
discovers the linear pull request stack connected to a target PR, then restacks
each PR parent-to-child without merging anything. Without a target, it uses the
pull request for the current branch.
.PP
The command composes
.BR git-pr-stack (1)
and
.BR git-pr-restack (1)
so force-with-lease push behavior stays centralized in the single-PR restack
primitive.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-b, \-\-base " branch
Rebase the root PR onto this base branch.
.TP
.B \-\-no-push
Rebase locally without pushing or editing PR bases.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry-run
Print actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Stack was synced.
.TP
.B 1
Stack discovery or restack failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-restack (1),
.BR git-pr-land-stack (1)
